<TEXT>
horseradish eaten during traditional passover 
dinners can pose a health hazard says a jewish doctor whose father 
collapsed after consuming an olivesized serving of the bitter herb 
dr haya r rubin said friday that her father cleveland state 
university sociologist israel rubin quickly recovered after he 
fainted keeled over and suffered a small seizure during a seder 
or traditional passover meal several years ago 
she said the incident shows that people prone to high blood 
pressure heart or artery disease or stroke might be better off if 
they let horseradish fumes evaporate by keeping it uncovered for a 
half hour before the seder or use a substitute such as chopped 
romaine lettuce stalks 
rubin suffered high blood pressure before the incident said his 
daughter an internist at the university of california los 
angeles and consultant to the rand corp 
the passover holiday which celebrates the israelites exodus 
from slavery in ancient egypt extends from friday night until 
sundown april 9 seders are held on the first two nights 
horseradish is eaten during the ceremonial meal as a bitter 
herb symbolizing the bitterness of slavery 
a letter warning that horseradish can be dangerous was published 
friday in the journal of the american medical association by ms 
rubin and dr albert w wu a clinical instructor at the university 
of california san diego 
wu said the horseradishinduced sudden loss of blood pressure 
that caused rubin to faint and collapse could trigger a fatal 
stroke heart attack or abnormal heart rhythm in people with heart 
disease 
wu and ms rubin trained together at mount sinai medical center 
in new york they decided to write the letter after wu spotted a 
letter about a similar incident published in the same journal in 
january 
in that letter dr daniel e spitzer of montefiore hospital in 
new york told how a healthy 63yearold man collapsed after eating 
a large mound of wasabi or greencolored japanese horseradish 
during a meal of sushi 
spitzers letter was headlined horseradish horrors sushi 
syncope syncope means fainting the followup letter by ms 
rubin and wu carried the headline the bitter herbs of seder more 
on horseradish horrors 
ms rubin said horseradish usually is grated but the night her 
father collapsed the family ground it in a food processor then 
placed it in an airtight container preventing vapors from escaping 
and making the horseradish unusually potent 
wu said the collapse probably occurred because the horseradish 
vapors caused a reflexive drop in blood pressure coupled with the 
elder rubins consumption of passover wine and use of medicine to 
reduce his high blood pressure that briefly deprived the brain of 
enough blood 
he still eats horseradish ms rubin said my dad is sort 
of macho 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

