<TEXT>
restoration work on rembrandts danae which 
was cut and splashed with acid by an attacker in 1985 has revealed 
how the dutch painter reworked the 17th century masterpiece the 
tass news agency said saturday 
restoration experts in leningrad using xrays ultraviolet and 
infrared light have completed the first stage of their work and 
now are getting ready to retouch the areas where the original paint 
was destroyed the report said 
a case history of hundreds of pages has been recorded tass 
said 
the painting was damaged june 15 1985 by what officials 
described as a madman who threw sulphuric acid on it and 
slashed it twice with a knife at leningrads hermitage museum 
soviet art officials have said the damage was serious but never 
have said specifically how much of the painting was destroyed 
restorers including chemists biologists physicists and other 
scientists began work immediately on the canvas the painting 
depicts the mother of perseus who according to greek legend 
killed medusa and her head of snakes 
soviet art books say rembrandt painted danae in 1636 and 
repainted it in 16461647 
xray studies showed that rembrandt had repainted the gesture 
of the right hand changed the appearance of the old woman looking 
from behind the canopy that he had painted over danaes earrings 
and beads and that he had altered her facial features several 
times in the course of the work tass said 
experts also established that the 81inch canvas was actually 
two pieces that had been skillfully sewn together covered first 
with a brown primer a layer of gray and then whiting 
it is our immutable principle not to paint over even a single 
millimeter of the authors painting yevgeny gerasimov head of 
the restoration effort told tass 
now we are beginning work on those sections where the layer of 
paint had been washed off and advancing from the sides of the 
painting to the four epicenters that suffered most from the acid 
we are drawing copies of danae to master rembrandts style he 
said 
the experts also tried to restore the paintings lacquer which 
had seriously deteriorated in several places tass said 
the report said experts would not speculate on when restoration 
work would be done but that they were confident the painting would 
be displayed once more in the hermitage when the work is completed 
