trade bill 
it is not a minute too soon our nations trade policy is in 
shambles you know it i know it we import more than we export we 
send more of our money overseas than we get back we are losing 
american jobs we are losing our industrial base we are in hock to 
foreign lenders 
once it wasnt so america traded hard all over the world the 
result was money in the bank and jobs for american workers america 
ran a trade surplus made in the usa was on the product that 
everybody looked for americans took pride in being no 1 
now our ability to compete is eroding for seven years the 
president has refused to act free trade he says what about 
fair trade the president has done nothing but cry protectionism 
and wave his veto pen yet unless we change the way america trades 
the tide of change will sweep our economic destiny out of our hands 
you know what i am talking about you see it in the frustration 
of all the young families who cannot afford to buy their first 
home you understand it when american companies take their jobs 
overseas 
