bill we are not ready to say goodbye to the america of our 
dreams what must be done to rebuild americas dreams 
first america must boost its exports selling more goods 
overseas lowers the deficit it is that simple our bill gives the 
president new tools to open new markets for american products 
second we must take steps to promote americas long run 
competitive strengths we want to see more investment in 
individuals and in ideas that means a better educated work force 
stronger laws to protect american inventions from piracy by foreign 
firms 
third we want to give american industry and workers the 
opportunity to retool and retrain quickly i have seen the 
devastating impact in my own state of west virginia where closed 
factories leave workers and whole communities struggling for their 
economic future 
this trade bill sharply improves the opportunities for workers 
to retrain to start new careers if american workers want to move 
to expanding parts of the job market they ought to have that chance 
finally this trade bill would prevent foreign investors from 
dominating industries vital to our national security america 
cannot control its destiny if our foreign competition is buying up 
our assets 
opening new markets for exports giving american industry a leg 
up to retool creating new opportunities for american workers to 
retrain keeping americas destiny in american hands educating our 
children for a prosperous future these are the essentials of this 
trade bill which the president would veto 
