foleys and bostonbased filenes department stores to may 
department stores co 
federateds discount and specialty store chains and its 
supermarkets divisions are expected to go on the block however 
morosky said after we comple te our review we might choose to 
keep certain divisions 
campeau wants to sell some of the divisions to pay off debt 
incurred in the federated purchase and to simplify operations 
morosky said 
thomas tashjian an analyst with the los angeles investment firm 
seidler amdec securities inc said recently that if campeau sells 
federateds units to larger companies such as may it would 
continue the trend toward central control and sameness 
however he said if the stores are sold to smaller companies or 
to entrepreneurial management groups it would mean increased 
competition which in turn leads to growth in the retail industry 
the longterm benefit is to the consumer tashjian said 
morosky said campeau already has received inquiries from 
retailers existing management and real estate developers about 
some of the federated stores he said the stores would go on sale 
several days after the purchase of federated is completed 
