the oil extended from the area of madison in southeastern 
indiana to louisville 
indiana conservation authorities also helped in the search 
mosher added barge fleets towboats and holding tanks along the 
river were all being checked 
mosher said the water was too choppy for an attempt to contain 
the oil slick 
